org.smartfrog.services.xunit.serial
Class TestInfo

java.lang.Object
  org.smartfrog.services.xunit.serial.TestInfo
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable
public final class TestInfo
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable

This is information about a test that is sent over the wire. One of the problems here is that even 'success' can be qualified, so that Prolog unit tests can say 'suceeded, but with multiple solutions', or a timed test could have 'succeeded out of time'
